sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant KRBP as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant REST as rest-container<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP

    Note over Client,PG: Flow 1: Model Registry API Access (External via Route)

    Client->>Router: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Router->>KRBP: HTTPS/8443<br/>TLS reencrypt
    KRBP->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>KRBP: Authorized
    KRBP->>REST: HTTP/8080<br/>localhost (no TLS)
    REST->>PG: TCP/5432<br/>Password auth<br/>SSL configurable
    PG-->>REST: Query Results
    REST-->>KRBP: JSON Response
    KRBP-->>Router: HTTPS Response
    Router-->>Client: HTTPS Response

    Note over Client,PG: Flow 2: Model Registry CR Reconciliation

    participant Operator as Operator Controller

    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event<br/>(ModelRegistry CR change)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: HTTPS/443<br/>SA Token<br/>Create/Update resources<br/>(Deployment, Service, SA,<br/>Role, RoleBinding, Route,<br/>NetworkPolicy, ConfigMap)
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Resource created/updated

    Note over Client,PG: Flow 3: Model Catalog Reconciliation

    participant MCR as ModelCatalogReconciler

    K8sAPI->>MCR: Watch event<br/>(ConfigMap/ModelRegistry change)
    MCR->>K8sAPI: HTTPS/443<br/>SA Token<br/>Read Auth CR,<br/>Create catalog resources
    K8sAPI-->>MCR: Resources reconciled
